All Implemented Interfaces:
com.esotericsoftware.kryo.KryoSerializable, com.telenav.kivakit.core.value.count.Countable, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.code.TripwireTrait, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.collection.Emptiness, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.collection.Sized, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.lifecycle.Initializable, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.naming.Nameable, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.naming.NamedObject, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.numeric.Zeroable, PackedPrimitiveArray, CompressibleCollection, LongIterable, LongList, PrimitiveList, LongCollection
public final class SplitPackedArray extends PrimitiveSplitArray implements LongList, PackedPrimitiveArray
SplitPackedArray maintains an array of packed arrays, indexing them as a single larger array. The purpose in this is to avoid resizing as a very large packed array grows. Instead, when a write index is greater than the size of the SplitPackedArray, a new PackedArray is allocated and added to the list. This design is similar to the "rope" pattern for handling very large strings.
Author:
jonathanl (shibo)
